# TRIVY IGNORE FILE
# This file suppresses security findings that have been reviewed and accepted as "Calculated Risks."

# AWS-0104: Security group rule allows unrestricted egress to any IP address.
# Justification: EKS Nodes require outbound access to reach public container registries (ECR, DockerHub) 
# and AWS APIs. In a future iteration, this will be hardened using VPC Endpoints and a private registry.
# --- Infrastructure / Network ---
AWS-0104 # Unrestricted egress - Required for pulling images/updates during node bootstrap

# --- Toolchain / Docker ---
DS-0002 # Root user - Required for GitHub Actions runner compatibility and workspace permissions
DS-0026 # Healthcheck - Not applicable for CLI toolchains (non-daemon containers)

# --- Global / Upstream Noise ---
AVD-AWS-0105 # NACL allows all ports - Default behavior in terraform-aws-modules/vpc
AVD-AWS-0040 # EKS public access - Business requirement for Dev/Learning environment
AVD-AWS-0038 # EKS public endpoint - Business requirement for Dev/Learning environment
AVD-AWS-0088 # S3 Encryption - Learning environment (using default encryption for simplicity)
DS-0010     # apt-get recommends - Toolchain optimization (not critical for CI container)
